<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When using decorators a Image Element is rendered as a Text Element</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$image = new Zend_Form_Element_Image('submitImage');
$image-&gt;setLabel('')
    -&gt;setValue('test.gif')
    -&gt;setAttrib('class', 'button');
$form-&gt;addElement($image);
        
$form-&gt;setElementDecorators(array(
    array('ViewHelper'),
    array('Errors'),
    array('HtmlTag', array('tag' =&gt; 'dd')),
    array('Label', array('tag' =&gt; 'dt')),
));
</code></pre>

<p></p>

<p>A quick look at the image attributes shows the helper is defined as fromText
var_dump($image-&gt;getAttribs());</p>

<p>Outputs:
array(2) { ["helper"]=&gt; string(8) "formText" ["class"]=&gt; string(6) "button" }</p>

